Step 2: The 3D Data Structure (The Thesis Upgrade)
In Phase 1, your data was a 2D spreadsheet: [Samples, Features].
Now, your data becomes a 3D Tensor: [Samples, Time_Steps, Features].
Samples: The total number of video clips (e.g., 1,000 videos).
Time_Steps: The 30 consecutive frames of movement per video.
Features: Your streamlined Kinematic numbers (Centered Coordinates + Joint Angles) extracted from each frame.
