🧠 Things to Keep in Mind (The "Thesis" Details)
The Padding & Interpolation Problem: What if a video of "Thank You" is signed very fast and only lasts 20 frames, but your AI demands exactly 30?
Basic Fix: Zero-Padding (filling the remaining 10 frames with zeros at the end of the array).
Thesis Fix: Temporal Interpolation. Mathematically stretch the 20 frames to 30 frames by calculating the average distance between the known frames. This is a massive flex for your research paper and proves you understand time-series data.
Temporal Augmentation (Synthetic Diversity): To prevent your AI from memorizing one specific signing speed, artificially multiply your dataset. Write logic that randomly drops 2 or 3 frames from a 30-frame sequence and duplicates others to maintain the 30-frame count. This perfectly simulates different human signing speeds without needing to record new videos.
Dataset Size Management: 3D data gets massive instantly. For example, 1,000 videos $\times$ 30 frames $\times$ 100 features = 3,000,000 data points. Using numpy.save() compresses this highly dimensional geometry efficiently into a single .npy file, whereas a CSV would crash your computer.

